- Flags, when used, shall be red or fluorescent orange-red in color, shall be a minimum of 24 inches square, and shall be securely fastened to a staff that is approximately 3 6 inches in length.
- The free edge of a flag should be weighted so the flag will hang vertically, even inheavy winds.
- When used at nighttime, flags shall be retroreflectorized.
- Flaggers shall use a STOP/SLOW paddle, a flag, or an Automated Flagger Assistance Device (AFAD) (see Sections 6L.02 through 6L.04) to control road users approaching a TTC zone. The use of hand movements is illustrated in Figure 6D-1.[[SRC_1]]

