PROMPT 82: What does PROWAG require for detectable warning surface size and color?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- The detectable warning surface area shall be yellow and shall match SAE AMS Standard 595, color number 33538.
- When painting a detectable warning surface is required, such as on a steel detectable warning surface, the yellow paint shall conform to Section 9-08.1(8) and shall match SAE AMS Standard 595, color number 33538.
- The detectable warning surface shall extend 24 inches (610 mm) minimum in the direction of pedestrian travel.
- At curb ramps and blended transitions, detectable warning surfaces shall extend the full width of the curb ramp run (excluding any flared sides), blended transition, or landing.
- At cut-through pedestrian refuge islands, detectable warning surfaces shall extend the full width of the pedestrian circulation path opening.
- At pedestrian at-grade rail crossings not located within a street, detectable warning surfaces shall extend the full width of the pedestrian circulation path.
- Where required at boarding platforms, detectable warning surfaces shall extend the full width of the pedestrian circulation path.[[SRC_3]]

