PROMPT 85: What are ADA requirements for accessible parking space dimensions and slope?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- Accessible parking spaces shall be at least 96 in (2440 mm) wide.
- Parking spaces and access aisles shall be level with surface slopes not exceeding 1:48.
- Changes in level are not permitted.
- Access aisles shall be at the same level as the parking spaces they serve.
- EXCEPTION: Slopes not steeper than 1:48 shall be permitted.[[SRC_2]][[SRC_4]]

