PROMPT 98: What does ASCE 7 specify for wind pressure design on highway sign structures?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- Wind loads during construction must be calculated according to ASCE-7-16 (section 6.15 of Chapter 6).
- Utilize section 29.3 of ASCE 7-16 to calculate the wind load as shown in FigureE.14.
- W = Fh = qhGCfAf (lbs) (29.4-2, ASCE 7)
- Design wind pressure is based on an extreme value distribution of maximum annual wind velocities.
- The return period of extreme wind events is used to determine nominal loads forwind design.
- Nominal loads for extreme load cases/strength limit states are intended to be determined similarly to the approach used for wind design in ASCE 7.[[SRC_7]]

